    "title": "Bitcoin Core slowly increase RAM use and RAM is not released on shutdown.",
    "body": "Bitcoin Core slowly increase RAM use during first-run syncronization and RAM is not released on shutdown.\r\nOnly a cold reboot of the computer restore the RAM as unused.\r\nTime will tell if the problem continues after initial syncronisation is completed.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nBitcoin Core use a \"resonable\" amount of RAM during initial syncronation **and** completely releases the RAM on shutdown.\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior**\r\n\r\n![Skærmbillede 2021-01-10 162655](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3484684/104127196-feb25d00-5360-11eb-8431-190bfbd6cc4b.png)\r\n\r\n**To reproduce**\r\n\r\nI have shut the program down and restarted it several times and the problem persists.\r\n\r\n**System information**\r\n\r\nBitcoin Core vc0.20.1 downloaded from bitcoincore.org\r\nWindows 10 fully up to date. 32 Gb RAM, 512 Gb M.2 system disk",
